1. Mac OSX or Ubuntu
   =================

	a. Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/GoCast/gocastmain.git
	b. Download the Chromium Depot Tools [http://www.chromium.org/developers/how-tos/install-depot-tools].
	c. Run ./getdeps.sh to download dependencies (If the script breaks, run: ./getdeps.sh webrtc).
	d. Run ./prepdeps.sh Debug|Release to build the webrtc library.
	e. Run ./prepplugin.sh Debug|Release to build the plugin project using Firebreath 
	   [http://www.firebreath.org/].
	f. Run ./buildplugin.sh Debug|Release to generate GCP.plugin (Mac) or npGCP.so (Ubuntu).

2. Windows 7+
   ==========

	a. Install MSysGit [http://msysgit.github.io/].
	b. Download the Chromium Depot Tools [http://www.chromium.org/developers/how-tos/install-depot-tools].
	c. Set up your VS2010 development environment by following these instructions 
	   [http://www.chromium.org/developers/how-tos/build-instructions-windows].
	d. Clone the plugin repository: git clone https://github.com/GoCast/webrtc_plugin.git
	e. Open a git-bash terminal and run ./getdeps.sh to download dependencies.
	f. Go to deps/libjingle/trunk and run: 
	   python build/gyp_chromium --depth=. third_party/webrtc/build/merge_libs.gyp
	g. Open third_party/webrtc/build/merged_lib.sln in Visual Studio 2010.
	h. Open dllentry.cpp in the winsdk_samples project, and comment out the functions DllCanUnloadNow() and 
	   DllGetClassObjects().
	i. Build the project merged_lib
	j. Open a Windows command prompt, go to the repository folder and run: deps\firebreath\prepcmd2010.exe 
	   src\js_api\projects build
	k. Open build\Firebreath.sln and build the project GCPWixInstall. The plugin install file will be 
	   build\bin\GCP\Debug|Release\GCP.exe.
